[src:supercompilation/optimizing-compiler] When the loop variables index into an array, such a transformation can improve the locality of reference, depending on the array's layout.
[src:supercompilation/optimizing-compiler] If a quantity is computed inside a loop during every iteration, and its value is the same for each iteration, it can vastly improve efficiency to hoist it outside the loop and compute its value just once before the loop begins.
[src:supercompilation/optimizing-compiler] This is particularly important with the address-calculation expressions generated by loops over arrays.
