[src:supercompilation/optimizing-compiler] Instruction scheduling is an important optimization for modern pipelined processors, which avoids stalls or bubbles in the pipeline by clustering instructions with no dependencies together, while being careful to preserve the original semantics.
[src:supercompilation/optimizing-compiler] Rematerialization recalculates a value instead of loading it from memory, eliminating an access to memory.
